description:
Schroeder's is a great German gastropub to kick back, grab a beer (Das Boot, anyone?), and eat a few sausages. The spacious seating arrangement and shareable menu items are quite conducive to large groups, so I would recommend coming with a bunch of friends. That way, you can all appreciate the over-the-top Bavarian decor together. The vibe is casual, energetic, and upscale - a perfect fit in FiDi. Come to Schroeder's not for its authenticity, but for its awesome ambiance. Oh, and its really good mustard.

// Vesperplatte ($24) - 3 stars
// Sausage Platter ($40) - 4 stars
// Smothered Tots ($12) - 3 stars
